But what, my dear, will become of us now?ÑLovelace not only reform'd, but turn'd preacher!ÑWhat will become of us now?ÑWhy, my sweet friend, your <i>generosity</i> is now engaged in turn'd favour!ÑFie, upon this <i>Generosity!</i>ÑI think in my heart, that ÑI does as much mischief to the noble-minded, as <i>Love</i> to the ignobler.ÑWhat before was only a <i>conditional liking,</i> I am now afraid will turn to <i>liking unconditional.</i>             I could not endure to turn my invective into panegyric all at once, and so soon.
