So I made still farther inquiry after his life and manners, and behaviour there, in hopes to find something bad: But all uniform!
Upon the Whole, Mr. Lovelace comes out with so much advantage from this inquiry, that were there the least room for this inquiry, I should suspect the Whole to be a plot set on foot to wash a blackmoor white.
Adieu, my dear.
ANNA HOWE.
